        "title": "Fix Kimi tool-call rewriting stop reason handling",
        "body": "\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior or issue addressed: Prevented Kimi response normalization from rewriting assistant-origin tool-call messages so that `stopReason` remains on the assistant flow instead of being treated as a generic tool-initiated completion.\nReal environment tested: Real OpenClaw checkout in a local Windows environment running OpenClaw tooling (`pnpm`, `node`, `vitest`) against the provider extension test suite after patching `extensions/kimi-coding/stream.ts`.\nExact steps or command run after the patch:\n- Set `OPENCLAW_VITEST_INCLUDE_FILE=[\"kimi-coding/stream.test.ts\"]`.\n- Run `pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest.extension-providers.config.ts`.\nAfter-fix evidence: Terminal output from the real run:\n```text\n$env:OPENCLAW_VITEST_INCLUDE_FILE='[\"kimi-coding/stream.test.ts\"]'\n> pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest.extension-providers.config.ts\n\n✓ extensions/kimi-coding/stream.test.ts (17 tests)\n  ✓ Kimi extension › stream response normalization › preserves assistant stopReason for tool-call messages\n  ✓ Kimi extension › stream response normalization › preserves assistant path when tool-call message arrives late\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  17 passed (17)\n   Start at  ...\n   Duration  ...\n```\nObserved result after fix: In this regression scope, assistant-role messages that contain tool calls remain on the assistant flow with `stopReason` preserved as expected; user-facing behavior no longer shows assistant messages rewritten to `toolUsed` stop reason.\nWhat was not tested: No screenshot/video terminal capture was collected, and full cross-platform real-provider end-to-end replay was not run in this proof pass.",
